MIME-Version: 1.0
Content-Type: text/plain; charset=UTF-8
Content-Transfer-Encoding: 8bit

After deep debugging of TH-U popup hang, drag-drop crash, and
random crash signatures on Android + FEX-Emu:

* Patch 020 (RtlWait / SleepCV drain): narrowed to drain only on
  STATUS_TIMEOUT (not STATUS_ALERTED) AND only when not inside a
  WindowProc dispatch (NtUserGetThreadInfo()->recursion_count == 0).
  The ALERTED branch + re-entrant dispatch were triggering TH-U's
  drag-drop NULL-this crash at TH-U+0x1802DF0C3 by dispatching
  cross-thread sends inside the worker's mid-flight windowproc.
  SleepConditionVariableSRW path keeps draining regardless of depth
  (its drain exists *specifically* to break in-windowproc deadlocks).

* Patch 014 (WM_MOUSEACTIVATE for top_level_child): narrowed to fire
  only when the active window actually changes (matches upstream
  wine condition shape). Removed the per-click cross-thread send
  that perturbed TH-U's MessageManager↔worker timing.

* Patch 025 (server-side focus-cycle detector): kept the original
  5-message filter ({WM_SETFOCUS, WM_KILLFOCUS, WM_ACTIVATE,
  WM_ACTIVATEAPP, WM_NCACTIVATE}) — tested narrowing to just
  SETFOCUS/KILLFOCUS but popup interaction froze (WM_ACTIVATE
  variant was load-bearing).

* Patch 013 (NtUserSetFocus allow top-level WS_CHILD): reverted.
  No regression observed; patches 014/015/021 cover the JUCE focus
  paths sufficiently.

